<p>Since the changes in the dielectric permittivity tensor of the PSLC (PDLC) sample, caused by the recording processes, are small relative to the unperturbed state [
 <xref rid="B31-polymers-11-00861" ref-type="bibr">31</xref>,
 <xref rid="B32-polymers-11-00861" ref-type="bibr">32</xref>,
 <xref rid="B33-polymers-11-00861" ref-type="bibr">33</xref>,
 <xref rid="B34-polymers-11-00861" ref-type="bibr">34</xref>], it is possible to present the resulting distribution of perturbed dielectric permittivity tensor in the form:
 <disp-formula id="FD6-polymers-11-00861">
  <label>(6)</label>
  <math id="mm63">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mi>for</mi>
     <mo> </mo>
     <mi>PSLC</mi>
     <mo> </mo>
     <mo>–</mo>
     <mo> </mo>
     <mover accent="true">
      <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">ε</mi>
      <mo>^</mo>
     </mover>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal">
        <mi>r</mi>
       </mstyle>
       <mo>,</mo>
       <mi>t</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
     <mn>1</mn>
     <mo>−</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">ρ</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
     <mrow>
      <mo>[</mo>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">ε</mi>
        <mi>p</mi>
       </msub>
       <mo>⋅</mo>
       <mover accent="true">
        <mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi>
        <mo>^</mo>
       </mover>
       <mo>+</mo>
       <mstyle displaystyle="true">
        <munderover>
         <mo>∑</mo>
         <mrow>
          <mi>m</mi>
          <mo>=</mo>
          <mi>o</mi>
          <mo>,</mo>
          <mi>e</mi>
         </mrow>
         <mrow/>
        </munderover>
        <mrow>
         <mo>Δ</mo>
         <msubsup>
          <mover accent="true">
           <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">ε</mi>
           <mo>^</mo>
          </mover>
          <mi>p</mi>
          <mi>m</mi>
         </msubsup>
         <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mrow>
           <mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal">
            <mi>r</mi>
           </mstyle>
           <mo>,</mo>
           <mi>t</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mo>)</mo>
         </mrow>
        </mrow>
       </mstyle>
      </mrow>
      <mo>]</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo>+</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">ρ</mi>
     <mrow>
      <mo>[</mo>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mover accent="true">
         <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">ε</mi>
         <mo>^</mo>
        </mover>
        <mrow>
         <mi>l</mi>
         <mi>c</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
       <mo>+</mo>
       <mstyle displaystyle="true">
        <munderover>
         <mo>∑</mo>
         <mrow>
          <mi>m</mi>
          <mo>=</mo>
          <mi>o</mi>
          <mo>,</mo>
          <mi>e</mi>
         </mrow>
         <mrow/>
        </munderover>
        <mrow>
         <mo>Δ</mo>
         <msubsup>
          <mover accent="true">
           <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">ε</mi>
           <mo>^</mo>
          </mover>
          <mrow>
           <mi>l</mi>
           <mi>c</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mi>m</mi>
         </msubsup>
         <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mrow>
           <mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal">
            <mi>r</mi>
           </mstyle>
           <mo>,</mo>
           <mi>t</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mo>)</mo>
         </mrow>
         <mo>+</mo>
         <mo>Δ</mo>
         <msubsup>
          <mover accent="true">
           <mi mathvariant="sans-serif">ε</mi>
           <mo>^</mo>
          </mover>
          <mrow>
